snippet: In “Magical,” at New York Live Arts, the director Annie Dorsen and the choreographer Anne Juren tease and challenge feminist performance art of the 1960s and ’70s.
abstract: Brian Seibert reviews premiere of dance concert Magical, directed by Annie Dorsen and choreographed and performed by Anne Juren, at New York Live Arts as part of Performance Space 122's Coil festival.
lead_paragraph: In “Magical,” at New York Live Arts, the director Annie Dorsen and the choreographer Anne Juren tease and challenge feminist performance art of the 1960s and ’70s.

headline.seo: ‘Magical,’ by Annie Dorsen and Anne Juren, at New York Live Arts
